snippet.textDisplay:
I've been a youth basketball Coach for over ten years now, having the pleasure of Coaching my son and my daughter. I've been coaching my daughter, Lola, in basketball for five years now. She is an amazing person and basketball player. She just turned 13 on February 23rd. On the day of the helicopter crash, we'd just gotten home from a tough game when we heard the news. We were both still stung a bit from losing our game when the news on the radio and TV hit us.
Above tremendous sadness came perspective. A new perspective. A better perspective.
Thanks Kobe and Gianna for reminding me what life is really all about.
I've been coaching youth basketball for over ten years now. Last season I took on a second team, my first team without a child of mine on the roster. I've come to love coaching kids more than anything. I've been coaching girls for the passed 5 years and plan on continuing long into my future.
I think I'll have Kobe and Gianna on my mind before every practice and every game.
I'll cherish the time spent with my son and daughter as Coach and Player as I know those days are not forever.
Being their Dad is though.
Perspective. I've got it.
Thanks Kobe and Gianna. For everything.
Love, Coach Michael

snippet.textDisplay:
DEATH HAD NOT WON!!!

In moments like this, it feels it feels like death has won. But the Bible says that love is stronger than death. Your hearts are heavy, tears flow down. Your spirits are wounded. I feel that too.

I understand what it is to be in pain. You look around and everybody you love and everybody you can count on and everybody you can trust seems to be slipping through your fingers. And it feels as though death has won.

In the Bible, the first family, when Cain killed able, it seemed like death had won. In the Bible, Noah escaped the flood, however, Still he died. It looked like death had won.

In the Bible, Isaiah was an eagle-eye prophet, he could see thousands of miles and years away. Still he died. It looked like death had won.

In the Bible, Habaka had come as a prophet to Israel, spoke truth so powerful and so profound, but no matter how close he was to God, still he died. It looked like death had won.

We've seen scientists and
astronauts and politicians and great thinkers of the ages and no matter how profound and prolific or bright they were, still they died. It looked like death had won.

But the Bible kept saying that love is stronger than death. And like two gladiators in a fight. Every time THEY enter into the ring it looks like death has won...

Love rolled into the ring and said wait a minute, death. You've been bullying people for a long time. But I want to set the record straight. Love is greater than death.

But early Sunday morning, love rolled up his sleeves and said wait a minute, wait a minute, wait a minute. Snatched great death and took the sting out of death and the victory out the grave. I want you to understand in a very practical and pragmatic way that death has NOT won. In the Bible, Jesus was definitely proof that death has not won.

Your tears may flow. Your pain may come. The flowers will wither. The cards will all be filed away. The phone will stop ringing.

Mama said, they're going to stop ringing after a while. Cakes and pies all stop coming. Don't you dare think that death has won. You will learn what all of us know who have lost people that we love.

You'll be driving down the street one day and you'll hear Kobe's and GiGi's voice talking in your head. Something he or she said; or something he or she did will pop up in your spirit and you'll giggle inside to yourself as if he or she was sitting in the car with you.

And you will find the people that you really love, they may leave you outwardly, but they never leave you inwardly. May the love of God, the peace of the Holy Spirit, the sweet communion of knowing that you are a child of the king, keep you through this period in life when it might appear as if death has won, but it's alive my family and friends. Love will last forever, for God is love. KOBE/GIGI.. WE will miss you. Vanessa, our love is with you sis!!!

Pastor Dameian B., MBA and Yevette B., MSW
